biweekly.parameter

Class ICalParameters

  • java.lang.Object
    • biweekly.util.ListMultimap<String,String>
      • biweekly.parameter.ICalParameters
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Iterable<Map.Entry<String,List<String>>>

    public class ICalParameters
extends ListMultimap<String,String>
    Stores the parameters that belong to a property.
    Author:
    Michael Angstadt

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes

      class  ICalParameters.ICalParameterList<T>
      A list that converts the raw string values of a parameter to another kind of value (for example, Integers).

    • Field Detail

      • ALTREP

        public static final String ALTREP
        Contains a URI that points to additional information about the entity represented by the property.
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.14-5, Constant Field Values

      • CHARSET

        public static final String CHARSET
        Defines the character set that the property value is encoded in (for example, "UTF-8"). It is only used in the vCal 1.0 standard, and is typically used when a property value is encoded in quoted-printable encoding.
        See Also:
        vCal 1.0 p.16, Constant Field Values

      • CN

        public static final String CN
        Contains a human-readable, display name of the entity represented by this property (for example, "John Doe"). It is used by the Attendee and Organizer properties.
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.15-6, Constant Field Values

      • CUTYPE

        public static final String CUTYPE
        Used by the Attendee property. It defines the type of object that the attendee is (for example, an "individual" or a "room").
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.16, Constant Field Values

      • DELEGATED_FROM

        public static final String DELEGATED_FROM
        Used by the Attendee property. It stores a list of people who have delegated their responsibility to the attendee. The values must be URIs. They are typically email URIs (for example, "mailto:janedoe@example.com").
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.17, Constant Field Values

      • DELEGATED_TO

        public static final String DELEGATED_TO
        Used by the Attendee property. It stores a list of people to which the attendee has delegated his or her responsibility. The values must be URIs. They are typically email URIs (for example, "mailto:janedoe@example.com").
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.17-8, Constant Field Values

      • DIR

        public static final String DIR
        Contains a URI (such as an LDAP URI) which points to additional information about the person that the property represents. It is used by the Attendee and Organizer properties.
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.18, Constant Field Values

      • DISPLAY

        public static final String DISPLAY
        Used by the Image property. It defines the ways in which the client application should display the image (for example, as a thumbnail-sized image).
        See Also:
        draft-ietf-calext-extensions p.13, Constant Field Values

      • EMAIL

        public static final String EMAIL
        Used by the Attendee property. Normally, this property's value contains the email address of the attendee. But if the property value must hold something else, this parameter can be used to store the attendee's email address.
        See Also:
        draft-ietf-calext-extensions p.14, Constant Field Values

      • ENCODING

        public static final String ENCODING
        Defines how the property value is encoded (for example, "base64" for a binary value).
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.18-9, Constant Field Values

      • EXPECT

        public static final String EXPECT
        Used by the Attendee property. It defines whether the event organizer expects the attendee to attend or not. It is only used in the vCal 1.0 standard.
        See Also:
        vCal 1.0 p.25, Constant Field Values

      • FEATURE

        public static final String FEATURE
        Used by the Conference property. It defines the features that the conference supports (for example, audio and video).
        See Also:
        draft-ietf-calext-extensions p.15, Constant Field Values

      • FMTTYPE

        public static final String FMTTYPE
        Defines the content type of the property value (for example, "image/jpg" if the property value is a JPEG image).
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.19-20, Constant Field Values

      • FBTYPE

        public static final String FBTYPE
        Used by the FreeBusy property. It defines whether the person is "free" or "busy" over the time periods that are specified in the property value. If this parameter is not set, the user should be considered "busy" during these times.
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.20, Constant Field Values

      • LABEL

        public static final String LABEL
        Defines a human-readable label for the property.
        See Also:
        draft-ietf-calext-extensions-01 p.16, Constant Field Values

      • LANGUAGE

        public static final String LANGUAGE
        Defines the language that the property value is written in (for example, "en" for English).
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.21, Constant Field Values

      • MEMBER

        public static final String MEMBER
        Used by the Attendee property. It defines the groups that the attendee is a member of in the form of URIs. Typically, these are email URIs (for example, "mailto:mailinglist@example.com").
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.21-2, Constant Field Values

      • PARTSTAT

        public static final String PARTSTAT
        Used by the Attendee property. It defines the participation status of the attendee (for example, "ACCEPTED"). If none is defined, then the property should be treated as if this parameter was set to "NEEDS-ACTION".
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.22, Constant Field Values

      • RANGE

        public static final String RANGE
        Used by the RecurrenceId property. It defines the effective range of recurrence instances that the property references.
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.23-4, Constant Field Values

      • RELATED

        public static final String RELATED
        Used by the Trigger property. It defines the date-time field that the property's duration (if specified) is relative to (for example, the start date or the end date).
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.24, Constant Field Values

      • RELTYPE

        public static final String RELTYPE
        Used by the RelatedTo property. It defines the kind of relationship the property is describing (for example, a "child" relationship).
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.25, Constant Field Values

      • ROLE

        public static final String ROLE
        Used by the Attendee property. It defines the attendee's role and/or whether they must attend or not (for example, "OPT-PARTICIPANT" for "optional participant"). If none is defined, then the property should be treated as if this parameter was set to "REQ-PARTICIPANT" (required participant).
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.25, vCal 1.0 p.25, Constant Field Values

      • RSVP

        public static final String RSVP
        Used by the Attendee property. It defines whether the event organizer would like the attendee to reply with his or her intention of attending ("true" if the organizer would like a reply, "false" if not). If this parameter is not defined, then the property should be treated as if this parameter was set to "false".
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.26, vCal 1.0 p.25, Constant Field Values

      • SENT_BY

        public static final String SENT_BY
        Defines a URI which represents a person who is acting on behalf of the person that is defined in the property. Typically, the URI is an email URI (for example, "mailto:janedoe@example.com"). It is used by the Attendee and Organizer properties.
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.27, Constant Field Values

      • STATUS

        public static final String STATUS
        Used by the Attendee property. It defines the status of the person's event invitation (for example, "TENTATIVE" if the person may or may not attend). It is only used in the vCal 1.0 standard.
        See Also:
        vCal 1.0 p.25, Constant Field Values

      • TYPE

        public static final String TYPE
        Defines the content type of the property value (for example, "WAVE" for an audio file). It is only used in the vCal 1.0 standard.
        See Also:
        vCal 1.0 p.27, Constant Field Values

      • TZID

        public static final String TZID
        Used by properties that contain date-time values. It defines the timezone that the property value is formatted in. It either references a timezone defined in a VTIMEZONE component, or contains an Olson timezone ID. To use an Olson timezone ID, the parameter value must be prepended with a "/" (for example, "/America/New_York").
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.27-8, Constant Field Values

      • VALUE

        public static final String VALUE
        Defines the data type of the property value (for example, "date" if the property value is a date without a time component). It is used if the property accepts multiple values that have different data types.
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.29-50, Constant Field Values

      • ICalParameters

        public ICalParameters(Map<String,List<String>> map)

        Creates a parameter list that is backed by the given map. Any changes made to the given map will effect the parameter list and vice versa.

        Care must be taken to ensure that the given map's keys are all in uppercase.

        To avoid problems, it is highly recommended that the given map NOT be modified by anything other than this ICalParameters class after being passed into this constructor.

        Parameters:
        map - the map

      • getDelegatedFrom

        public List<String> getDelegatedFrom()

        Gets the DELEGATED-FROM parameter values.

        This parameter is used by the Attendee property. It stores a list of people who have delegated their responsibility to the attendee. The values must be URIs. They are typically email URIs (for example, "mailto:janedoe@example.com").

        Changes to the returned list will update the ICalParameters object, and vice versa.

        Returns:
        the URIs or an empty list if none are set
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.17

      • getMembers

        public List<String> getMembers()

        Gets the MEMBER property values.

        This parameter is used by the Attendee property. It defines the groups that the attendee is a member of in the form of URIs. Typically, these are email URIs (for example, "mailto:mailinglist@example.com").

        Changes to the returned list will update the ICalParameters object, and vice versa.

        Returns:
        the groups or empty list if none are set
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.21-2

      • getRsvp

      • getTimezoneId

        public String getTimezoneId()

        Gets the TZID (timezone ID) parameter value.

        This parameter is used by properties that contain date-time values. It defines the timezone that the property value is formatted in. It either references a timezone defined in a VTIMEZONE component, or contains an Olson timezone ID. To use an Olson timezone ID, the parameter value must be prepended with a "/" (for example, "/America/New_York").

        Returns:
        the timezone ID or null if not set
        See Also:
        RFC 5545 p.27-8

      • validate

        public List<ValidationWarning> validate(ICalVersion version)

        Checks the parameters for data consistency problems or deviations from the specification.

        These problems will not prevent the iCalendar object from being written to a data stream*, but may prevent it from being parsed correctly by the consuming application.

        *With a few exceptions: One thing this method does is check for illegal characters. There are certain characters that will break the iCalendar syntax if written (such as a newline character in a parameter name). If one of these characters is present, it WILL prevent the iCalendar object from being written.

        Parameters:
        version - the version to validate against
        Returns:
        a list of warnings or an empty list if no problems were found
